\fs20 \cf0 These notes apply to Ubuntu versions 10.04, 10.10, 11.04 & 11.10. See the end note regarding Ubuntu 12.04. There are different disk layouts discussed as well as the sets of packages needed for ESP-r to be compiled and run. If you are installing Ubuntu in a virtual machine or re-using an existing virtual machine for environments such as VirtualBox or Parallels the look at the last sections of the document.  Scanning this whole document before you begin is a 
\b really good idea
\b0 !\

