\b \cf0 Before you start
\b0 \
\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural

\fs20 \cf0 Have the following information available before you start:\
\
a) the disk space available and RAM  - Ubuntu can take as little as 6GB of disk space and will run with ~1GB of RAM. More memory (e.g. 2 or 3GB) will increase the speed of your assessments and results recovery tasks.  10GB of disk space is ok for general use in a virtual machine or computer with limited disk space.  Complex models can generate results files of 2-4GB so consider the scope of likely work to be carried out.\
\
b) the layout of the disk(s) and partition(s) on the machine - you may be wanting to dual-boot or to use a virtual drive so locate where space is available.  If you are dual booting with Windows install Linux after Windows.\
\
c) the IP address, machine name/domain, router etc.\
\
d) finish reading this document\

