\b0 \
\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural

\fs20 \cf0 To compile ESP-r requires additional software and libraries.  The package manager will list current and available packages in various formats.  You can also search for specific packages by name  e.g. ddd (a debugger) and groff (to convert some ESP-r documents into PS files).  In the list below are packages which you will need, they may already be included in your Linux distribution or be listed under a slightly different name.\
\
Install them via the following syntax:\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural

\b \cf0   sudo apt-get install build-essential\
  sudo apt-get install console-tools-dev\
  sudo apt-get install expect-dev\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural

\b0 \cf0   . . .\
\
You can also combine commands\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural

\b \cf0   sudo apt-get install build-essential console-tools-dev expect-dev\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural

\b0 \cf0 \
As the ESP-r community considers the GCC 4.4 compiler as the reference compiler you should consider which version of the GCC compilers to work with.  It is possible to have multiple compilers as long as you specify which compiler version to use in the Install command line (e.g. --compiler_version -4.4).\
\
Development:  build-essential, console-tools-dev, expect-dev, g++, gcc, gfortran, gdb,gettext, libtool, linux-headers, linux-source, subversion, libxml2, libxml2-dev, libxml2-utils libxslt1-dev libxslt1-dbg\
\
Gnome desktop: dia-gnome (a useful helper application)\
\
Graphics, netpbm (convert between graphics formats) imagemagick (screen grab & display)  gimp gimp-data\
\
Libraries: libx11-6-dbg, libx11-dev, \
\
Miscellaneous - Graphical: gsfonts-x11 xfonts-mplus  xfonts-terminus  xfonts-terminus-dos  xfonts-100dpi xfs font-manager\
\
Networking: gfrtp-gtk, openssh-server, ssh\
\
Shells: csh\
\
Word processing: enscript, psutils nedit nedit-dbg\
\
For GTK development selecting the libgtk2.0-dev package will identify most of the dependencies you are likely to need. To assist with debugging also ask for the -dbg versions of the libraries such as:\
libfontconfig1-dbg, libcairo2-dbg, libpixman-1-0-dbg, libxslt1-dbg, libgtk2.0-0-dbg\
\
A fresh install of Ubuntu 11.04 is missing a number of the fonts which were available in earlier versions of Ubuntu. If the X11 interface will not start or the GTK wireframe control crashes then this is likely because of missing fonts.\
\
To force a refresh of the font cache do the following:\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural

\b \cf0   sudo dpkg-reconfigure fontconfig-config\
  sudo fc-cache -f -v\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural

\b0 \cf0 \
To find out the fonts installed on your computer you can use the command:\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural

\b \cf0   fc-list\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural

\b0 \cf0 \
To find out about the compilers (gcc g++ and gfortran) use commands such as:\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural

\b \cf0   which gcc\
  ls -l /usr/bin/gc*\
  gcc --version\
  which gfortran\
  l s -l /usr/bin/gfor*\
  gfortran --version\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural

\b0 \cf0 There may be several versions of gcc on your machine.  The gcc --version command tells you the specifics.\

